  <text>
      <body>
        
     
      <div xml:id="sonnet"> 
              <interpGrp type="poembox">
                <interp ana="#form" type="sonnet"></interp>
                <interp ana="#tone" type="other"></interp>
                <interp ana="#topic" type="love"></interp>
              </interpGrp>
             <lg> 
              <l>He courts her with Soir de Paris &amp; braids myths in her hair.</l>
          <l>To hear time how they need it to be is the sound of dare.</l> 
          <l>His soft-burned tenor soaks her like grapes in wild yeast.</l>
          <l>A beatiful loser, she takes pleasure in being incomplete.</l>
          <l>He draws tears from grown men when he plucks his box.</l>
          <l>She is reckles, never trained, so mouch a wound clock.</l>
          <l>They move like movement in a still life picture.</l>
          <l>She sings behind the beat and leans into the future.</l>
          <l>Stepping out of sequence as though they've just begun.</l>
          <l>Then again, the start moves back, depending on the run.</l>
                 
